<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203557>
    dc:description "FIGURE 52. The external morphology and polyps of Chrysogorgia pendula Versluys, 1902, specimen MBM286360. A, B. The same specimen in situ and after collection. C. Two non-terminal polyps filled with eggs under a light microscope. D, F. Single terminal polyps under a light microscope and SEM, respectively. E. A single non-terminal polyp filled with eggs under SEM. G. A part of branch under SEM. Scale bars: 5 cm (B); 1 mm (C–F); 300 μm (G)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203557/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203595>
    dc:description "FIGURE 66. The external morphology and polyps of Chrysogorgia pendula Versluys, 1902, specimen MBM286869. A, B. The same specimen in situ and after collection. C, F, G. Single non-terminal polyps under a light microscope and SEM, respectively. D, E, H. Single terminal polyps under a light microscope and SEM, respectively. I. Polyp body wall covered with flexible filaments. Scale bars: 5 cm (B); 1 mm (C–H), 500 μm (I)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203595/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203601>
    dc:description "FIGURE 68. The external morphology and polyps of Chrysogorgia pendula Versluys, 1902, specimen MBM286865. A, C. The same specimen in situ and after collection. B. Single non-terminal polyps under a light microscope. D. Small polyps on the stem under a light microscope. E, F. Single terminal polyps under a light microscope and SEM, respectively. G. A part of branch under SEM. H. Basal polyp body wall under SEM. Scale bars: 5 cm (C); 1 mm (B, D–F); 200 μm (G, H)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203601/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

